\begin_layout Subsection
Treatments
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This experiment is designed to measure whether workers discrininate in reciproci
ty based on the race of the employer and which economic theory explains
 the source of discrimination.
 The experiment is a 2-factor design with treatments as follows; 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Baseline Treatment
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this treatment, we rely on a version of bilateral gift-exchange game
 in which each participant play the game 10 times/periods 
\begin_inset ERT
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
citep{Fehr1998}
\end_layout

\end_inset

.
 This is a two-person game consisting of two stages.
 In the first stage, an employer decide how much wage to offer to a worker.
 Worker observes the wage offer in the second stage and choose effort level.
 Effort is costly to workers but profitable to employers.
 Wage is costly to employer but profitable to worker.
 All earnings in the experiment will be calculated in the unit of points
 which will be converted to US dollars at the end of experiment with the
 exchange rate of 
\begin_inset Formula $1\text{ point}=10\text{ cents}$
\end_inset

.
 The effort cost function is specified as in Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Effort-Cost"

\end_inset

; 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float table
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center

